.TH DBX-HOST 1 "2026-06-06" "dbx 0.30.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-host \- interactively add a backup host to config.json
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx host add
.SH DESCRIPTION
Interactively prompt for a new host's connection parameters and write
them to
.IR config.json .
Uses
.B gum
when available for a polished TUI; falls back to plain
.B read
prompts otherwise.
.PP
Prompts cover:
.IP \(bu 2
Alias (key in
.IR .hosts ).
.IP \(bu 2
DB type (postgres, mysql, mariadb).
.IP \(bu 2
Hostname / IP, port.
.IP \(bu 2
Username; optional password (stored in the system keychain via
.BR dbx-vault (1),
not in plain text in config).
.IP \(bu 2
Optional SSH tunnel (jump host, port, key path).
.IP \(bu 2
Optional
.IR safety
flag (prod / stage / local).
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
dbx host add
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dbx/config.json
The host block is appended under
.IR .hosts[alias] .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-config (1),
.BR dbx-vault (1),
.BR dbx-test (1).
